				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$|y| < 2$\end{document}. This region is not directly relevant for air showers as shown in Fig. 15. It has not been shown experimentally yet that these effects can also be seen in hadrons produced at forward rapidities. Theoretical calculations suggest that hadrons produced from QGP decay reach well into the forward region, in p-p at 13TeV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
